From: nvidia-driver-injector <noreply@example.invalid>
Date: 2026-05-12
Subject: [PATCH 0005/0007] tb-egpu: close-path observability (cluster P4)

Consolidates legacy 0029 (RM-side close-path DIAG) and 0030 (UVM-side
close-path DIAG) into one close-path observability cluster.

What this cluster IS: the markers + state snapshot infrastructure for
the close-path bug class (docs/architecture.md Problem 2 + Problem 4).
The bug class is currently mitigated observationally (per memory
project_close_path_mitigated_2026_05_08 — close-path-probe.sh n=3
proven), not by a code fix. These markers are how we know the
mitigation stays in place under future stack changes. Passive
instrumentation only (ioremap+ioread32 + PCI config-space reads).

What this cluster is NOT: the recovery state machine (P2), the
qwatchdog (P3), or the recovery-state DIAG hookups (P6, Kconfig-gated).
The err_handlers callbacks from legacy 0029 (mmio_enabled +
cor_error_detected) already landed in P2 as part of the err_handlers
struct registration.

Inventory items applied (per docs/patch-refactor-inventory.md "### P4"):

- Renames:
    tb_egpu_lever_m_close_path_diag   -> tb_egpu_close_diag
    tb_egpu_lever_m_diag_dump_pdev    -> tb_egpu_close_diag_pdev
    aorus_uvm_close_path_diag         -> tb_egpu_uvm_close_diag_*
                                         (split into 5 site-named
                                          helpers per inventory's
                                          "extract atomic patterns")
    aorus_uvm_get_gpu_pdev            -> tb_egpu_get_gpu_pdev
                                         (now lives in nvidia.ko and
                                          is EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL — the
                                          legacy "extern in uvm.c"
                                          pattern is gone)
    aorus_uvm_fd_count                -> tb_egpu_uvm_fd_count
    log prefix "AORUS Lever M-recover [CLOSE]" / "AORUS UVM [CLOSE]"
                                      -> "tb_egpu [CLOSE]" / "tb_egpu UVM [CLOSE]"
    log prefix "AORUS Lever M-recover [UVM-DIAG]"
                                      -> "tb_egpu [UVM-DIAG]"

- Hardcoded BDF eliminated. Legacy 0030 hardcoded the GPU pdev lookup
  to pci_get_domain_bus_and_slot(0, 0x04, PCI_DEVFN(0,0)). Replaced
  with tb_egpu_get_gpu_pdev() — an EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL helper in
  nvidia.ko that walks nv_linux_devices under the global lock and
  returns the first NVIDIA pdev (refcount incremented; caller
  pci_dev_puts). Generalises to any PCI topology; single-GPU project
  scope preserved.

- void* type-erasure removed. Legacy 0030 declared the AER trigger
  helper as taking void *out in uvm.c (to avoid pulling the snapshot
  struct definition into nvidia-uvm). Refactor: UVM forward-declares
  struct tb_egpu_qwd_aer_snapshot as opaque and passes the typed
  pointer through. NULL is the legitimate value at every UVM call
  site (no per-call snapshot persistence on the UVM side).

- atomic_inc/read/dec patterns extracted into 5 site-named one-shot
  helpers (one per UVM lifecycle point). uvm.c call sites are now
  pure single-line calls — no inline atomic logic to repeat.

- New file pair for UVM-side helpers. Legacy 0030 inlined a 60+ line
  block of project code into uvm.c. Refactor moves it to
  kernel-open/nvidia-uvm/nv-tb-egpu-uvm.{c,h}. uvm.c's touch is now
  exactly: 1 include + 8 single-line call sites. Better cohesion;
  smaller blast radius into the vendor file.

- EXPORT_SYMBOL audit. UVM is a separate .ko (nvidia-uvm.ko), so the
  cross-module symbols are EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL (not EXPORT_SYMBOL):
    tb_egpu_dump_aer_trigger_event  (added — P2 left this internal-
                                     only; P4 needs it cross-module)
    tb_egpu_get_gpu_pdev            (new — pdev lookup helper)
    tb_egpu_close_diag_pdev         (new — pdev-based state capture)
  tb_egpu_close_diag (RM-side) is NOT exported — internal to nvidia.ko.

- Reuse of P2's WPR2 helper. tb_egpu_close_diag_pdev calls
  tb_egpu_recover_read_wpr2 (file-static in nv-tb-egpu-recover.c) for
  the WPR2 portion of its state capture, instead of open-coding
  ioremap+ioread32+iounmap a fourth time.

Cross-cluster dependencies:

- P4 declares tb_egpu_close_diag (RM-side) standalone — it captures
  full state via tb_egpu_close_diag_pdev (its own pdev-based variant),
  NOT via P6's recover_diag_dump. This sidesteps the P6 dependency
  that the legacy structure would have implied: P4 lands fully
  functional without P6.

- P4 promotes P2's tb_egpu_dump_aer_trigger_event to
  EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL. P2's commit message said "internal to nvidia.ko"
  which was true at P2's apply time; P4 extends the visibility because
  nvidia-uvm.ko now consumes the symbol. Both states are self-consistent
  at their respective apply times.

Five UVM call sites (uvm.c):

  uvm-open-entry        end of uvm_open success path; pre-increment
                        fd_count==0 ⇒ first-after-LAST-CLOSE
  uvm-release-entry     top of uvm_release before any teardown
  uvm-pre-destroy       VA_SPACE branch only, just before
                        uvm_va_space_destroy
  uvm-post-destroy      VA_SPACE branch only, just after
                        uvm_va_space_destroy
  uvm-release-exit      end of uvm_release; post-decrement
                        fd_count==0 ⇒ canonical LAST-CLOSE

Four RM-side call sites (nv.c):

  close-entry           top of nvidia_close_callback after nvl check
  pre-stop              just before nv_close_device under ldata_lock
  post-shutdown         inside nv_stop_device after teardown
  close-exit            end of nvidia_close_callback

Files touched:
  kernel-open/nvidia/nv-tb-egpu-recover.c          +154
    (EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL on existing dump_aer_trigger_event,
     three new functions: get_gpu_pdev, close_diag_pdev, close_diag)
  kernel-open/nvidia/nv-tb-egpu-recover.h          +45/-2 (decls + doc)
  kernel-open/nvidia/nv.c                          +45  (4 call sites)
  kernel-open/nvidia-uvm/nv-tb-egpu-uvm.c          new  (129 lines)
  kernel-open/nvidia-uvm/nv-tb-egpu-uvm.h          new  (35 lines)
  kernel-open/nvidia-uvm/uvm.c                     +16  (include + 5 call sites)
  kernel-open/nvidia-uvm/nvidia-uvm-sources.Kbuild +1   (source entry)

Validation: git apply --check vs vanilla 595.71.05 with P1+P5+P3+P2
stacked OK; container build (refactor-rc1) OK.

Userspace + close-path-probe.sh references the legacy log prefixes —
updates scoped to Phase 4.

